<HEADLINE>
HSINCHU MAYOR INTRODUCES GLASS MUSEUM TO EUROPEAN TV REPORTER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 8 (CNA) 02/08/07  20:50:13 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
Hsinchu Mayor Lin Jung-tse introduced the Hsinchu Municipal Glass
Museum in the northern city Thursday to a reporter from a
European cable TV channel visiting to do a segment on Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
EuroNews journalist Margitta Kirstaedter was also scheduled to
cover the National Palace Museum, the official noted.
</P>
<P>
Lin received the journalist with the city's Bureau of Cultural
Affairs Deputy Director-General Lin Rong-chou, Glassman Society
Chairwoman Huang Bao-shue, and Hsinchu Wind City Glass Artist
Association Chairman Hsu Yuan-rong.
</P>
<P>
Lin Jung-tse explained that in earlier times, the glass craft in
the city was limited to industrial glass production.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, however, the craft has transformed into an artform, he
said.
</P>
<P>
EuroNews is a European cable television network broadcasting to
189 million households in 121 countries every day in seven
languages -- French, English, German, Italian, Spanish,
Portuguese and Russian.
</P>
